sentence: The S&P 500 and the Nasdaq hit record highs on Wednesday as investors bought into technology stocks that have thrived during the COVID-19 pandemic following the upbeat quarterly results from Salesforce and HP Enterprise.
ET, the Dow Jones Industrial Average .DJI was down 0.15% at 28,205.74.
The S&P 500 .SPX was up 0.41% at 3,457.81 and the Nasdaq Composite .IXIC was up 1.07% at 11,589.454.

The top three S&P 500 .PG.INX percentage gainers: ** Salesforce.Com Inc <CRM.N>, up 25.8% ** Netflix Inc <NFLX.O>, up 7.7% ** Adobe Inc <ADBE.O>, up 6.9% The top three S&P 500 .PL.INX percentage losers: ** Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings <NCLH.N>, down 4.8% ** Occidental Petroleum Corp <OXY.N>, down 3.5% ** Simon Property Group Inc <SPG.N>, down 3.4% The top three NYSE .PG.N percentage gainers: ** Anaplan Inc <PLAN.N>, up 29% ** Salesforce.Com Inc <CRM.N>, up 25.8% ** Dick's Sporting Goods Inc <DKS.N>, up 15.2% The top three NYSE .PL.N percentage losers: ** Garret Motion Inc <GTX.N>, down 42% ** Phoenix Tree Holdings Ltd <DNK.N>, down 16% ** K12 Inc <LRN.N>, down 13.2% The top three Nasdaq .PG.O percentage gainers: ** Cryoport Inc <CYRX.O>, up 33.4% ** Fluidigm Corp <FLDM.O>, up 32.4% ** Scworx Corp <WORX.O>, up 28.2% The top three Nasdaq .PL.O percentage losers: ** Xpresspa Group Inc <XSPA.O>, down 16.7% ** Urban One Inc <UONE.O>, down 14.5% ** Kelly Services Inc <KELYB.O>, down 14.3% ** Salesforce.com Inc CRM.N: up 25.7%
